A New York based Engineering Company is looking for an Engineer experienced in technical translation (Russian/English). The core subject area is oil refinery and technology. The ideal candidate will also have software product knowledge.

Job Requirements: 

- proficiency in both Russian and English;
- proofreading other content types that need technical validation;
- relevant translation experience in the related areas (a test/sample translation may be requested);
- grammatical and contextual accuracy and ability to meet deadlines;
- Bachelor's degree, obtained in Russia preferred;
- detail-oriented, deadline-driven, and organized;
- knowledge of Auto-CAD.

Contact information:

Please email your resume and a brief cover letter showing your name and contacts.

Thank you!


Laberge Group is seeking motivated and talented applicants for a Civil Engineering position to assist the Engineering Department.  Must be energetic with excellent communication & technical skills, knowledge of commonly used concepts, practices, and procedures in AutoCAD Civil 3D with relevant work experience in stormwater management, drinking water and sewer utilities, site design. desired.  Typical project types include water, wastewater, site development, dam rehabilitation, and storm water management.

JOB DUTIES INCLUDE:
•	Concept design drawings;
•	Design drawings;
•	Detailing various design components;
•	Assisting with technical specifications;
•	Field survey reduction & mapping;
•	Grading and erosion control plans; and
•	Assistance to Project Engineers and Project Managers to prepare and complete project documents.

EDUCATION, EXPERIENCE, AND OTHER REQUIREMENTS
•	 AAS degree or higher preferred;
•	Be able to work independently and in a team environment;
•	Have basic knowledge regarding water, sewer, grading and stormwater; and
•	Valid Driver's license.

Laberge Group has provided engineering, surveying, planning and community development services since 1964 to public and private sector clients.  Our diverse portfolio of successfully completed project, coupled with an experienced core of project management and design staff, provides clients creative, integrated and distinctive solutions. We are large enough to be professionally exhilarating and challenging, and small enough to provide highly attentive service to our clients.

This is an opportunity to join a growing, well established firm which offers a competitive salary commensurate with experience as well as an excellent benefit package.  

All replies will be held in confidence.  Interested candidates should send a detailed resume including education, work history and experience with emphasis on the elements identified above along with salary requirements. Laberge Group is an Equal Opportunity Employer - M/F/Veteran/Disability.
